1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:13,000
It was rather interesting just to watch them gathering their materials and bouncing around their, what do they call it, kangaroo walk or something like that.

2
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Who named it that? I don't know.

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:19,000
I bet those men are going to get quite a reception when they get back.

4
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Yes, I'll be so glad when they land back now, but I think that's pretty well a fact because they've landed so many safely now that I feel relieved.

5
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Just getting off of the moon was the thing that was...

6
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,000
Have they met with the one that was circling?

7
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:54,000
They've rendezvoused, so I understand. That wasn't shown either, but they say they have rendezvoused, so that's a matter of making the circles and then coming down.

8
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:58,000
What do you sort of imagine for the future? Do you imagine them sending up ships?

9
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:22,000
I think they will. I think they will do some more exploring up there because that was such a very small area when you think of it that they just gathered rocks and samples of soil and all, and they did probe for some samples.

10
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:26,000
And just what's going to come of that, I don't know. I'd be glad to read it.

